Fairweather Johnson - Hootie & The Blowfish [1996]
	

Fairweather Johnson is the second studio album by the band Hootie & the Blowfish, released on April 23, 1996. The album has been certified triple-platinum in the US. Three songs from the album were released as singles: "Old Man & Me", "Tucker's Town", and "Sad Caper". The album debuted at #1 on the Billboard 200 album sales chart in May 1996. Though it has since gone triple platinum, this is significantly less than their previous effort, Cracked Rear View, which went platinum sixteen times.
